Special thanks to thn81, L42y, City-Busz, and all of the other AUR maintainers that helped make it possible to run Unity under Arch Linux!

Please make sure you don't already have modified versions of the dependencies installed. For example, gtk3-ubuntu might fail to compile if there's a modified version of gtk3 already installed.

Packages ending with "-ubuntu" contain Ubuntu patches and REPLACE Arch Linux versions of those packages.

Order to compile/install:

01: glib2-ubuntu                   -> glib 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
02: gtk2-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 2.0 with Ubuntu patches
03: gtk3-ubuntu                    -> GTK toolkit 3.0 with Ubuntu patches
04: qt-ubuntu                      -> Qt toolkit with Ubuntu patches
05: gconf-ubuntu                   -> A configuration database system
06: libdbusmenu                    -> Library for passing menus over DBus
07: libindicator                   -> Symbols and functions for indicators
08: libindicate                    -> Libraries for apps to raise 'flags' on DBus
09: libindicate-qt                 -> Qt bindings for libindicate
10: libappindicator                -> Library to export menu bar to Unity
11: appmenu-gtk                    -> Application menu module for GTK+
12: bamf                           -> Application matching framework
13: libqtbamf                      -> Qt bindings for bamf
14: dee                            -> Create Model-View-Controller apps over DBus
15: libqtdee                       -> Qt binding and QML plugin for Dee
16: libqtgconf                     -> Qt bindings for GConf
17: dconf-qt                       -> Qt bindings for DConf
18: sni-qt                         -> Turns Qt tray icons into appindicators
19: ido                            -> Widgets and objects used for indicators
20: libzeitgeist                   -> Client library to interact with Zeitgeist
21: zeitgeist-datahub              -> Plugins that insert events into Zeitgeist
22: geoclue                        -> Modular geoinformation service
23: python2-geoclue                 -> Geoclue Python module
24: python2-xapian                  -> Python bindings for Xapian
25: zeitgeist-extensions           -> Extensions for Zeitgeist
26: gnome-activity-journal         -> Tool for easily browsing and finding files
27: gsettings-desktop-schemas      -> Shared GSettings schemas for the desktop
28: gnome-settings-daemon-ubuntu   -> Daemon handling the GNOME session settings
29: gnome-session-ubuntu           -> GNOME Session Manager
30: pulseaudio-ubuntu              -> A featureful, general-purpose sound server
31: gnome-control-center-ubuntu    -> Utilities to configure the GNOME desktop
32: gnome-screensaver-ubuntu       -> Screensaver and screen locking for GNOME
33: metacity-ubuntu                -> Lightweight GTK+ window manager
34: launchpad-integration          -> Launchpad.net integration
35: indicator-applet               -> GNOME panel indicator applet
36: indicator-application          -> Takes menus and puts then in the panel
37: indicator-appmenu              -> An indicator to host the menus from apps
38: libtimezonemap                 -> GTK+3 timezone map widget
39: indicator-datetime             -> A very, very simple clock
40: indicator-messages             -> Collects messages that need a response
41: indicator-multiload            -> Port of the GNOME multiload applet
42: indicator-power                -> Indicator to show battery information
43: indicator-session              -> Indicator to manage session
44: indicator-sound                -> A unified sound menu
45: network-manager-applet-ubuntu  -> Network Manager applet with indicator support
46: gnome-bluetooth-ubuntu         -> Gnome bluetooth applet with indicator support
47: gtest                          -> C++ testing utility based on xUnit
48: gmock                          -> A library for writing C++ mock classes
49: overlay-scrollbar *            -> Overlay scrollbars for GTK 2 and GTK 3
50: plasma-widget-menubar *        -> KDE Plasma widget to display menubar
51: xfce4-indicator-plugin *       -> XFCE panel plugin to display indicators
52: utouch-evemu                   -> Event emulation for the uTouch stack
53: utouch-frame                   -> Touch frame library
54: fixesproto-ubuntu              -> X11 Fixes extension wire protocol
55: libxfixes-ubuntu               -> X11 misc. 'fixes' extension library
56: xorg-server                    -> Xorg X server
57: check                          -> Unit testing framework for C
58: utouch-grail                   -> Gesture recognition and instantiation lib.
59: utouch-geis                    -> Implementation of the GEIS interface
60: nux                            -> An OpenGL toolkit
61: unity-asset-pool               -> Design assets for Unity
62: gnome-menus2                   -> Gnome menu specifications
63: libunity                       -> Library for integrating Unity
64: libunity-misc                  -> Differently licensed stuff for Unity
65: nautilus-ubuntu                -> File manager and graphics shell for GNOME
66: unity-lens-applications        -> Unity applications lens
67: unity-lens-files               -> Unity files lens
68: unity-lens-music               -> Unity music lens
69: unity-lens-video               -> Unity video lens
70: compiz-core-ubuntu             -> Compiz core components
71: libcompizconfig-ubuntu         -> Compiz configuration system library
72: compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu * -> GConf backend for Compiz
73: compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu * -> KConfig4 backend for Compiz
74: compizconfig-python-ubuntu     -> Compizconfig bindings for Python
75: ccsm-ubuntu                    -> Compiz configuration manager
76: compiz-plugins-main-ubuntu     -> Compiz main plugins
77: compiz-plugins-extra-ubuntu    -> Compiz extra plugins
78: unity-core *                   -> Parts of Unity 3D needed for Unity 2D
79: unity                          -> A desktop experience designed for efficiency
80: unity-2d                       -> 2D implementation of Unity

* Optional packages
  - overlay-scrollbar              => For GNOME/Unity users who want a space saving scrollbar
  - plasma-widget-menubar          => For KDE users who want a global menubar
  - xfce4-indicator-plugin         => Ayatana indicators plugin for the XFCE panel
  - compizconfig-backend-gconf-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in GConf
  - compizconfig-backend-kconfig4-ubuntu => Store Compiz settings in KConfig4
  - unity-core                     => For users that want Unity 2D, but not Unity 3D

All of PKGBUILD's were checked by namcap for consistency. The binary packages have not been checked yet.

Troubleshooting:

Global menus aren't working when logging in with KDM (KDE display manager).

  This happens because previous versions of KDM weren't patched to source the
  /etc/X11/xinit/xinitrc.d/ directory. This is fixed in kdebase-workspace version
  4.7.2-1, but requires the KDM configuration files to be regenerated (resetting
  all KDM configuration options). To regenerate the configuration files, run as root

    # rm -rvf /usr/share/config/kdm
    # genkdmconf

AHH! Something is wrong with Unity!

  Try resetting the settings for Unity and Compiz and relogin:

    $ rm -rvf ~/.compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.config/compiz-1/
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compiz-1
    $ gconftool-2 --recursive-unset /apps/compizconfig-1
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compiz-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.gconf/apps/compizconfig-1/
    $ rm -rvf ~/.cache/unity/
    $ rm -vf ~/.cache/unity-lens-video

  If something is still wrong, please file a bug report at either:

    https://github.com/chenxiaolong/Unity-for-Arch/issues

  or

    https://bugs.launchpad.net/unity-for-arch
